Package com.hp.hpl.jena.eyeball.loaders

Interface Summary
Loader A Loader is just a class that can load a model on being given the "name" of that model.
 

Class Summary
FileLoader A FileLoader wraps a FileManager, providing only the load(String) method, and intercepting names of the form "via:ROOT@FILE" to load the model described by ROOT in the assembly file FILE.
JDBCLoader Answer the RDB model which has the given name in the given database specified by a jdbc URL.
JDBCSensitiveLoader A JDBCSensitiveLoader will pick one of two laoders, depending on whether the URI it's offered starts with jdbc: or not.
OntLoader An OntLoader loads ontology models given their URIs, relying on a base Loader for the base model.
